  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is aimed to examine the value of incisional negative pressure therapy after
      resection of soft tissue tumors. Its a prospective randomized trial comparing incisional
      negative pressure to standard wound dressings.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Wound healing after resection of large soft tissue tumors is often impaired by large dead
      space and fluid collection, potentially resulting in seroma formation and infection. Aim of
      the study is to compare negative pressure wound therapy to standard wound dressing in terms
      of quantity of drainage fluid and wound healing complications.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
